FBIS3-9221 "dreeu055__a94016" FBIS-EEU-94-055-A Document Type:Daily Report 18 Mar 1994 ANNEX Hungary Romanian Ship Held After Violating UN Embargo AU1803184294 Budapest MTI in English 1747 GMT 18 Mar 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU1803184294 Budapest MTI Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Budapest, 18 March (MTI) -- A Romanian river freighter was held up at Mohacs on the south Hungarian stretch of the Danube due to its violation of UN sanctions against rump Yugoslavia, local customs authorities told MTI. The ship, Slobozia Mare, arrived at Mohacs on Monday [14 March] with Budapest as its destination. When checked thoroughly for compliance of embargo regulations, it was found to be carrying only 18 tonnes of oil instead of the 52 tonnes indicated in its official documents, with water replacing the missing quantity. According to unconfirmed information, the Romanian captain and the crew of two Serbs and six Ukrainians admitted to having sold the missing oil, worth 2.7 million forints ($1 equals 103 forints), in Serbia. Customs investigations are continuing.
